{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Each of you possesses"},{"time":2000,"text":"the most powerful, dangerous and subversive trait"},{"time":5000,"text":"that natural selection has ever devised."},{"time":8000,"text":"It's a piece of neural audio technology"},{"time":11000,"text":"for rewiring other people's minds."},{"time":13000,"text":"I'm talking about your language, of course,"},{"time":16000,"text":"because it allows you to implant a thought from your mind"},{"time":19000,"text":"directly into someone else's mind,"},{"time":22000,"text":"and they can attempt to do the same to you,"},{"time":24000,"text":"without either of you having to perform surgery."},{"time":27000,"text":"Instead, when you speak,"},{"time":29000,"text":"you're actually using a form of telemetry"},{"time":31000,"text":"not so different"},{"time":33000,"text":"from the remote control device for your television."},{"time":35000,"text":"It's just that, whereas that device"},{"time":37000,"text":"relies on pulses of infrared light,"},{"time":39000,"text":"your language relies on pulses,"},{"time":42000,"text":"discrete pulses, of sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44000,"text":"And just as you use the remote control device"},{"time":47000,"text":"to alter the internal settings of your television"},{"time":49000,"text":"to suit your mood,"},{"time":51000,"text":"you use your language"},{"time":53000,"text":"to alter the settings inside someone else's brain"},{"time":55000,"text":"to suit your interests."},{"time":57000,"text":"Languages are genes talking,"},{"time":59000,"text":"getting things that they want."},{"time":61000,"text":"And just imagine the sense of wonder in a baby"},{"time":64000,"text":"when it first discovers that, merely by uttering a sound,"},{"time":67000,"text":"it can get objects to move across a room"},{"time":69000,"text":"as if by magic,"},{"time":71000,"text":"and maybe even into its mouth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74000,"text":"Now language's subversive power"},{"time":76000,"text":"has been recognized throughout the ages"},{"time":78000,"text":"in censorship, in books you can't read,"},{"time":80000,"text":"phrases you can't use"},{"time":82000,"text":"and words you can't say."},{"time":84000,"text":"In fact, the Tower of Babel story in the Bible"},{"time":87000,"text":"is a fable and warning"},{"time":89000,"text":"about the power of language."},{"time":91000,"text":"According to that story, early humans developed the conceit"},{"time":94000,"text":"that, by using their language to work together,"},{"time":96000,"text":"they could build a tower"},{"time":98000,"text":"that would take them all the way to heaven."},{"time":100000,"text":"Now God, angered at this attempt to usurp his power,"},{"time":103000,"text":"destroyed the tower,"},{"time":106000,"text":"and then to ensure"},{"time":108000,"text":"that it would never be rebuilt,"},{"time":110000,"text":"he scattered the people by giving them different languages --"},{"time":113000,"text":"confused them by giving them different languages."},{"time":116000,"text":"And this leads to the wonderful irony"},{"time":118000,"text":"that our languages exist to prevent us from communicating."},{"time":121000,"text":"Even today,"},{"time":123000,"text":"we know that there are words we cannot use,"},{"time":125000,"text":"phrases we cannot say,"},{"time":127000,"text":"because if we do so,"},{"time":129000,"text":"we might be accosted, jailed,"},{"time":132000,"text":"or even killed."},{"time":134000,"text":"And all of this from a puff of air"},{"time":136000,"text":"emanating from our mouths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"Now all this fuss about a single one of our traits"},{"time":141000,"text":"tells us there's something worth explaining."},{"time":143000,"text":"And that is how and why"},{"time":145000,"text":"did this remarkable trait evolve,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and why did it evolve"},{"time":149000,"text":"only in our species?"},{"time":151000,"text":"Now it's a little bit of a surprise"},{"time":153000,"text":"that to get an answer to that question,"},{"time":155000,"text":"we have to go to tool use"},{"time":157000,"text":"in the chimpanzees."},{"time":159000,"text":"Now these chimpanzees are using tools,"},{"time":161000,"text":"and we take that as a sign of their intelligence."},{"time":164000,"text":"But if they really were intelligent,"},{"time":166000,"text":"why would they use a stick to extract termites from the ground"},{"time":169000,"text":"rather than a shovel?"},{"time":171000,"text":"And if they really were intelligent,"},{"time":174000,"text":"why would they crack open nuts with a rock?"},{"time":176000,"text":"Why wouldn't they just go to a shop and buy a bag of nuts"},{"time":179000,"text":"that somebody else had already cracked open for them?"},{"time":182000,"text":"Why not? I mean, that's what we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"Now the reason the chimpanzees don't do that"},{"time":186000,"text":"is that they lack what psychologists and anthropologists call"},{"time":189000,"text":"social learning."},{"time":191000,"text":"They seem to lack the ability"},{"time":193000,"text":"to learn from others"},{"time":195000,"text":"by copying or imitating"},{"time":197000,"text":"or simply watching."},{"time":199000,"text":"As a result,"},{"time":201000,"text":"they can't improve on others' ideas"},{"time":203000,"text":"or learn from others' mistakes --"},{"time":205000,"text":"benefit from others' wisdom."},{"time":207000,"text":"And so they just do the same thing"},{"time":209000,"text":"over and over and over again."},{"time":211000,"text":"In fact, we could go away for a million years and come back"},{"time":215000,"text":"and these chimpanzees would be doing the same thing"},{"time":218000,"text":"with the same sticks for the termites"},{"time":220000,"text":"and the same rocks to crack open the nuts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223000,"text":"Now this may sound arrogant, or even full of hubris."},{"time":226000,"text":"How do we know this?"},{"time":228000,"text":"Because this is exactly what our ancestors, the Homo erectus, did."},{"time":231000,"text":"These upright apes"},{"time":233000,"text":"evolved on the African savanna"},{"time":235000,"text":"about two million years ago,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and they made these splendid hand axes"},{"time":239000,"text":"that fit wonderfully into your hands."},{"time":241000,"text":"But if we look at the fossil record,"},{"time":243000,"text":"we see that they made the same hand axe"},{"time":246000,"text":"over and over and over again"},{"time":248000,"text":"for one million years."},{"time":250000,"text":"You can follow it through the fossil record."},{"time":252000,"text":"Now if we make some guesses about how long Homo erectus lived,"},{"time":254000,"text":"what their generation time was,"},{"time":256000,"text":"that's about 40,000 generations"},{"time":259000,"text":"of parents to offspring, and other individuals watching,"},{"time":262000,"text":"in which that hand axe didn't change."},{"time":264000,"text":"It's not even clear"},{"time":266000,"text":"that our very close genetic relatives, the Neanderthals,"},{"time":268000,"text":"had social learning."},{"time":270000,"text":"Sure enough, their tools were more complicated"},{"time":273000,"text":"than those of Homo erectus,"},{"time":275000,"text":"but they too showed very little change"},{"time":277000,"text":"over the 300,000 years or so"},{"time":280000,"text":"that those species, the Neanderthals,"},{"time":282000,"text":"lived in Eurasia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"Okay, so what this tells us"},{"time":286000,"text":"is that, contrary to the old adage,"},{"time":289000,"text":"\"monkey see, monkey do,\""},{"time":292000,"text":"the surprise really is"},{"time":294000,"text":"that all of the other animals"},{"time":296000,"text":"really cannot do that -- at least not very much."},{"time":299000,"text":"And even this picture"},{"time":301000,"text":"has the suspicious taint of being rigged about it --"},{"time":304000,"text":"something from a Barnum &amp; Bailey circus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"But by comparison,"},{"time":308000,"text":"we can learn."},{"time":310000,"text":"We can learn by watching other people"},{"time":313000,"text":"and copying or imitating"},{"time":315000,"text":"what they can do."},{"time":317000,"text":"We can then choose, from among a range of options,"},{"time":320000,"text":"the best one."},{"time":322000,"text":"We can benefit from others' ideas."},{"time":324000,"text":"We can build on their wisdom."},{"time":326000,"text":"And as a result, our ideas do accumulate,"},{"time":329000,"text":"and our technology progresses."},{"time":333000,"text":"And this cumulative cultural adaptation,"},{"time":338000,"text":"as anthropologists call"},{"time":340000,"text":"this accumulation of ideas,"},{"time":342000,"text":"is responsible for everything around you"},{"time":344000,"text":"in your bustling and teeming everyday lives."},{"time":346000,"text":"I mean the world has changed out of all proportion"},{"time":348000,"text":"to what we would recognize"},{"time":350000,"text":"even 1,000 or 2,000 years ago."},{"time":353000,"text":"And all of this because of cumulative cultural adaptation."},{"time":356000,"text":"The chairs you're sitting in, the lights in this auditorium,"},{"time":358000,"text":"my microphone, the iPads and iPods that you carry around with you --"},{"time":361000,"text":"all are a result"},{"time":363000,"text":"of cumulative cultural adaptation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365000,"text":"Now to many commentators,"},{"time":369000,"text":"cumulative cultural adaptation, or social learning,"},{"time":372000,"text":"is job done, end of story."},{"time":375000,"text":"Our species can make stuff,"},{"time":378000,"text":"therefore we prospered in a way that no other species has."},{"time":381000,"text":"In fact, we can even make the \"stuff of life\" --"},{"time":384000,"text":"as I just said, all the stuff around us."},{"time":386000,"text":"But in fact, it turns out"},{"time":388000,"text":"that some time around 200,000 years ago,"},{"time":391000,"text":"when our species first arose"},{"time":393000,"text":"and acquired social learning,"},{"time":395000,"text":"that this was really the beginning of our story,"},{"time":397000,"text":"not the end of our story."},{"time":399000,"text":"Because our acquisition of social learning"},{"time":402000,"text":"would create a social and evolutionary dilemma,"},{"time":405000,"text":"the resolution of which, it's fair to say,"},{"time":408000,"text":"would determine not only the future course of our psychology,"},{"time":412000,"text":"but the future course of the entire world."},{"time":414000,"text":"And most importantly for this,"},{"time":417000,"text":"it'll tell us why we have language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420000,"text":"And the reason that dilemma arose"},{"time":422000,"text":"is, it turns out, that social learning is visual theft."},{"time":425000,"text":"If I can learn by watching you,"},{"time":428000,"text":"I can steal your best ideas,"},{"time":430000,"text":"and I can benefit from your efforts,"},{"time":433000,"text":"without having to put in the time and energy that you did"},{"time":435000,"text":"into developing them."},{"time":437000,"text":"If I can watch which lure you use to catch a fish,"},{"time":440000,"text":"or I can watch how you flake your hand axe"},{"time":442000,"text":"to make it better,"},{"time":444000,"text":"or if I follow you secretly to your mushroom patch,"},{"time":447000,"text":"I can benefit from your knowledge and wisdom and skills,"},{"time":450000,"text":"and maybe even catch that fish"},{"time":452000,"text":"before you do."},{"time":454000,"text":"Social learning really is visual theft."},{"time":457000,"text":"And in any species that acquired it,"},{"time":459000,"text":"it would behoove you"},{"time":461000,"text":"to hide your best ideas,"},{"time":463000,"text":"lest somebody steal them from you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467000,"text":"And so some time around 200,000 years ago,"},{"time":470000,"text":"our species confronted this crisis."},{"time":473000,"text":"And we really had only two options"},{"time":476000,"text":"for dealing with the conflicts"},{"time":478000,"text":"that visual theft would bring."},{"time":480000,"text":"One of those options"},{"time":482000,"text":"was that we could have retreated"},{"time":485000,"text":"into small family groups."},{"time":487000,"text":"Because then the benefits of our ideas and knowledge"},{"time":490000,"text":"would flow just to our relatives."},{"time":492000,"text":"Had we chosen this option,"},{"time":494000,"text":"sometime around 200,000 years ago,"},{"time":497000,"text":"we would probably still be living like the Neanderthals were"},{"time":500000,"text":"when we first entered Europe 40,000 years ago."},{"time":503000,"text":"And this is because in small groups"},{"time":505000,"text":"there are fewer ideas, there are fewer innovations."},{"time":508000,"text":"And small groups are more prone to accidents and bad luck."},{"time":511000,"text":"So if we'd chosen that path,"},{"time":513000,"text":"our evolutionary path would have led into the forest --"},{"time":516000,"text":"and been a short one indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":518000,"text":"The other option we could choose"},{"time":520000,"text":"was to develop the systems of communication"},{"time":523000,"text":"that would allow us to share ideas"},{"time":525000,"text":"and to cooperate amongst others."},{"time":528000,"text":"Choosing this option would mean"},{"time":530000,"text":"that a vastly greater fund of accumulated knowledge and wisdom"},{"time":533000,"text":"would become available to any one individual"},{"time":536000,"text":"than would ever arise from within an individual family"},{"time":539000,"text":"or an individual person on their own."},{"time":543000,"text":"Well, we chose the second option,"},{"time":546000,"text":"and language is the result."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549000,"text":"Language evolved to solve the crisis"},{"time":551000,"text":"of visual theft."},{"time":553000,"text":"Language is a piece of social technology"},{"time":556000,"text":"for enhancing the benefits of cooperation --"},{"time":559000,"text":"for reaching agreements, for striking deals"},{"time":562000,"text":"and for coordinating our activities."},{"time":566000,"text":"And you can see that, in a developing society"},{"time":568000,"text":"that was beginning to acquire language,"},{"time":570000,"text":"not having language"},{"time":572000,"text":"would be a like a bird without wings."},{"time":574000,"text":"Just as wings open up this sphere of air"},{"time":577000,"text":"for birds to exploit,"},{"time":579000,"text":"language opened up the sphere of cooperation"},{"time":581000,"text":"for humans to exploit."},{"time":583000,"text":"And we take this utterly for granted,"},{"time":585000,"text":"because we're a species that is so at home with language,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"but you have to realize"},{"time":590000,"text":"that even the simplest acts of exchange that we engage in"},{"time":593000,"text":"are utterly dependent upon language."},{"time":596000,"text":"And to see why, consider two scenarios"},{"time":598000,"text":"from early in our evolution."},{"time":600000,"text":"Let's imagine that you are really good"},{"time":602000,"text":"at making arrowheads,"},{"time":604000,"text":"but you're hopeless at making the wooden shafts"},{"time":607000,"text":"with the flight feathers attached."},{"time":610000,"text":"Two other people you know are very good at making the wooden shafts,"},{"time":613000,"text":"but they're hopeless at making the arrowheads."},{"time":616000,"text":"So what you do is --"},{"time":618000,"text":"one of those people has not really acquired language yet."},{"time":621000,"text":"And let's pretend the other one is good at language skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"So what you do one day is you take a pile of arrowheads,"},{"time":626000,"text":"and you walk up to the one that can't speak very well,"},{"time":628000,"text":"and you put the arrowheads down in front of him,"},{"time":630000,"text":"hoping that he'll get the idea that you want to trade your arrowheads"},{"time":633000,"text":"for finished arrows."},{"time":635000,"text":"But he looks at the pile of arrowheads, thinks they're a gift,"},{"time":637000,"text":"picks them up, smiles and walks off."},{"time":640000,"text":"Now you pursue this guy, gesticulating."},{"time":642000,"text":"A scuffle ensues and you get stabbed"},{"time":644000,"text":"with one of your own arrowheads."},{"time":647000,"text":"Okay, now replay this scene now, and you're approaching the one who has language."},{"time":650000,"text":"You put down your arrowheads and say,"},{"time":652000,"text":"\"I'd like to trade these arrowheads for finished arrows. I'll split you 50/50.\""},{"time":655000,"text":"The other one says, \"Fine. Looks good to me."},{"time":657000,"text":"We'll do that.\""},{"time":660000,"text":"Now the job is done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":663000,"text":"Once we have language,"},{"time":665000,"text":"we can put our ideas together and cooperate"},{"time":667000,"text":"to have a prosperity"},{"time":669000,"text":"that we couldn't have before we acquired it."},{"time":672000,"text":"And this is why our species"},{"time":674000,"text":"has prospered around the world"},{"time":676000,"text":"while the rest of the animals"},{"time":678000,"text":"sit behind bars in zoos, languishing."},{"time":681000,"text":"That's why we build space shuttles and cathedrals"},{"time":684000,"text":"while the rest of the world sticks sticks into the ground"},{"time":686000,"text":"to extract termites."},{"time":688000,"text":"All right, if this view of language"},{"time":691000,"text":"and its value"},{"time":693000,"text":"in solving the crisis of visual theft is true,"},{"time":696000,"text":"any species that acquires it"},{"time":698000,"text":"should show an explosion of creativity and prosperity."},{"time":701000,"text":"And this is exactly what the archeological record shows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704000,"text":"If you look at our ancestors,"},{"time":706000,"text":"the Neanderthals and the Homo erectus, our immediate ancestors,"},{"time":709000,"text":"they're confined to small regions of the world."},{"time":712000,"text":"But when our species arose"},{"time":714000,"text":"about 200,000 years ago,"},{"time":716000,"text":"sometime after that we quickly walked out of Africa"},{"time":719000,"text":"and spread around the entire world,"},{"time":722000,"text":"occupying nearly every habitat on Earth."},{"time":725000,"text":"Now whereas other species are confined"},{"time":728000,"text":"to places that their genes adapt them to,"},{"time":731000,"text":"with social learning and language,"},{"time":733000,"text":"we could transform the environment"},{"time":735000,"text":"to suit our needs."},{"time":737000,"text":"And so we prospered in a way"},{"time":739000,"text":"that no other animal has."},{"time":741000,"text":"Language really is"},{"time":744000,"text":"the most potent trait that has ever evolved."},{"time":747000,"text":"It is the most valuable trait we have"},{"time":750000,"text":"for converting new lands and resources"},{"time":753000,"text":"into more people and their genes"},{"time":756000,"text":"that natural selection has ever devised."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758000,"text":"Language really is"},{"time":760000,"text":"the voice of our genes."},{"time":762000,"text":"Now having evolved language, though,"},{"time":764000,"text":"we did something peculiar,"},{"time":766000,"text":"even bizarre."},{"time":768000,"text":"As we spread out around the world,"},{"time":770000,"text":"we developed thousands of different languages."},{"time":773000,"text":"Currently, there are about seven or 8,000"},{"time":775000,"text":"different languages spoken on Earth."},{"time":778000,"text":"Now you might say, well, this is just natural."},{"time":780000,"text":"As we diverge, our languages are naturally going to diverge."},{"time":783000,"text":"But the real puzzle and irony"},{"time":785000,"text":"is that the greatest density of different languages on Earth"},{"time":788000,"text":"is found where people are most tightly packed together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792000,"text":"If we go to the island of Papua New Guinea,"},{"time":794000,"text":"we can find about 800 to 1,000"},{"time":797000,"text":"distinct human languages,"},{"time":799000,"text":"different human languages,"},{"time":801000,"text":"spoken on that island alone."},{"time":803000,"text":"There are places on that island"},{"time":805000,"text":"where you can encounter a new language"},{"time":807000,"text":"every two or three miles."},{"time":809000,"text":"Now, incredible as this sounds,"},{"time":811000,"text":"I once met a Papuan man, and I asked him if this could possibly be true."},{"time":814000,"text":"And he said to me, \"Oh no."},{"time":816000,"text":"They're far closer together than that.\""},{"time":819000,"text":"And it's true; there are places on that island"},{"time":821000,"text":"where you can encounter a new language in under a mile."},{"time":824000,"text":"And this is also true of some remote oceanic islands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"And so it seems that we use our language,"},{"time":830000,"text":"not just to cooperate,"},{"time":832000,"text":"but to draw rings around our cooperative groups"},{"time":835000,"text":"and to establish identities,"},{"time":837000,"text":"and perhaps to protect our knowledge and wisdom and skills"},{"time":840000,"text":"from eavesdropping from outside."},{"time":843000,"text":"And we know this"},{"time":845000,"text":"because when we study different language groups"},{"time":847000,"text":"and associate them with their cultures,"},{"time":849000,"text":"we see that different languages"},{"time":851000,"text":"slow the flow of ideas between groups."},{"time":854000,"text":"They slow the flow of technologies."},{"time":857000,"text":"And they even slow the flow of genes."},{"time":860000,"text":"Now I can't speak for you,"},{"time":862000,"text":"but it seems to be the case"},{"time":864000,"text":"that we don't have sex with people we can't talk to."},{"time":868000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":870000,"text":"Now we have to counter that, though,"},{"time":872000,"text":"against the evidence we've heard"},{"time":874000,"text":"that we might have had some rather distasteful genetic dalliances"},{"time":877000,"text":"with the Neanderthals and the Denisovans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":881000,"text":"Okay, this tendency we have,"},{"time":883000,"text":"this seemingly natural tendency we have,"},{"time":885000,"text":"towards isolation, towards keeping to ourselves,"},{"time":888000,"text":"crashes head first into our modern world."},{"time":891000,"text":"This remarkable image"},{"time":893000,"text":"is not a map of the world."},{"time":895000,"text":"In fact, it's a map of Facebook friendship links."},{"time":899000,"text":"And when you plot those friendship links"},{"time":901000,"text":"by their latitude and longitude,"},{"time":903000,"text":"it literally draws a map of the world."},{"time":906000,"text":"Our modern world is communicating"},{"time":908000,"text":"with itself and with each other"},{"time":910000,"text":"more than it has"},{"time":912000,"text":"at any time in its past."},{"time":914000,"text":"And that communication, that connectivity around the world,"},{"time":917000,"text":"that globalization"},{"time":919000,"text":"now raises a burden."},{"time":922000,"text":"Because these different languages"},{"time":924000,"text":"impose a barrier, as we've just seen,"},{"time":926000,"text":"to the transfer of goods and ideas"},{"time":928000,"text":"and technologies and wisdom."},{"time":930000,"text":"And they impose a barrier to cooperation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"And nowhere do we see that more clearly"},{"time":936000,"text":"than in the European Union,"},{"time":938000,"text":"whose 27 member countries"},{"time":941000,"text":"speak 23 official languages."},{"time":944000,"text":"The European Union"},{"time":946000,"text":"is now spending over one billion euros annually"},{"time":950000,"text":"translating among their 23 official languages."},{"time":953000,"text":"That's something on the order"},{"time":955000,"text":"of 1.45 billion U.S. dollars"},{"time":957000,"text":"on translation costs alone."},{"time":960000,"text":"Now think of the absurdity of this situation."},{"time":962000,"text":"If 27 individuals"},{"time":964000,"text":"from those 27 member states"},{"time":966000,"text":"sat around table, speaking their 23 languages,"},{"time":969000,"text":"some very simple mathematics will tell you"},{"time":971000,"text":"that you need an army of 253 translators"},{"time":975000,"text":"to anticipate all the pairwise possibilities."},{"time":979000,"text":"The European Union employs a permanent staff"},{"time":982000,"text":"of about 2,500 translators."},{"time":984000,"text":"And in 2007 alone --"},{"time":986000,"text":"and I'm sure there are more recent figures --"},{"time":988000,"text":"something on the order of 1.3 million pages"},{"time":991000,"text":"were translated into English alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994000,"text":"And so if language really is"},{"time":997000,"text":"the solution to the crisis of visual theft,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"if language really is"},{"time":1002000,"text":"the conduit of our cooperation,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"the technology that our species derived"},{"time":1007000,"text":"to promote the free flow and exchange of ideas,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"in our modern world,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"we confront a question."},{"time":1015000,"text":"And that question is whether"},{"time":1017000,"text":"in this modern, globalized world"},{"time":1019000,"text":"we can really afford to have all these different languages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"To put it this way, nature knows no other circumstance"},{"time":1025000,"text":"in which functionally equivalent traits coexist."},{"time":1030000,"text":"One of them always drives the other extinct."},{"time":1033000,"text":"And we see this in the inexorable march"},{"time":1035000,"text":"towards standardization."},{"time":1037000,"text":"There are lots and lots of ways of measuring things --"},{"time":1040000,"text":"weighing them and measuring their length --"},{"time":1042000,"text":"but the metric system is winning."},{"time":1044000,"text":"There are lots and lots of ways of measuring time,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"but a really bizarre base 60 system"},{"time":1050000,"text":"known as hours and minutes and seconds"},{"time":1052000,"text":"is nearly universal around the world."},{"time":1055000,"text":"There are many, many ways"},{"time":1057000,"text":"of imprinting CDs or DVDs,"},{"time":1059000,"text":"but those are all being standardized as well."},{"time":1062000,"text":"And you can probably think of many, many more"},{"time":1065000,"text":"in your own everyday lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067000,"text":"And so our modern world now"},{"time":1070000,"text":"is confronting us with a dilemma."},{"time":1072000,"text":"And it's the dilemma"},{"time":1074000,"text":"that this Chinese man faces,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"who's language is spoken"},{"time":1078000,"text":"by more people in the world"},{"time":1080000,"text":"than any other single language,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"and yet he is sitting at his blackboard,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"converting Chinese phrases"},{"time":1090000,"text":"into English language phrases."},{"time":1092000,"text":"And what this does is it raises the possibility to us"},{"time":1095000,"text":"that in a world in which we want to promote"},{"time":1097000,"text":"cooperation and exchange,"},{"time":1099000,"text":"and in a world that might be dependent more than ever before"},{"time":1102000,"text":"on cooperation"},{"time":1104000,"text":"to maintain and enhance our levels of prosperity,"},{"time":1107000,"text":"his actions suggest to us"},{"time":1109000,"text":"it might be inevitable"},{"time":1111000,"text":"that we have to confront the idea"},{"time":1113000,"text":"that our destiny is to be one world with one language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1116000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1126000,"text":"Matt Ridley: Mark, one question."},{"time":1128000,"text":"Svante found that the FOXP2 gene,"},{"time":1131000,"text":"which seems to be associated with language,"},{"time":1133000,"text":"was also shared in the same form"},{"time":1135000,"text":"in Neanderthals as us."},{"time":1137000,"text":"Do we have any idea"},{"time":1139000,"text":"how we could have defeated Neanderthals"},{"time":1141000,"text":"if they also had language?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1143000,"text":"Mark Pagel: This is a very good question."},{"time":1145000,"text":"So many of you will be familiar with the idea that there's this gene called FOXP2"},{"time":1148000,"text":"that seems to be implicated in some ways"},{"time":1151000,"text":"in the fine motor control that's associated with language."},{"time":1154000,"text":"The reason why I don't believe that tells us"},{"time":1156000,"text":"that the Neanderthals had language"},{"time":1158000,"text":"is -- here's a simple analogy:"},{"time":1161000,"text":"Ferraris are cars that have engines."},{"time":1164000,"text":"My car has an engine,"},{"time":1166000,"text":"but it's not a Ferrari."},{"time":1168000,"text":"Now the simple answer then"},{"time":1170000,"text":"is that genes alone don't, all by themselves,"},{"time":1172000,"text":"determine the outcome"},{"time":1174000,"text":"of very complicated things like language."},{"time":1176000,"text":"What we know about this FOXP2 and Neanderthals"},{"time":1178000,"text":"is that they may have had fine motor control of their mouths -- who knows."},{"time":1182000,"text":"But that doesn't tell us they necessarily had language."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184000,"text":"MR: Thank you very much indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1186000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}